parameters.text:
=Extract and structure the project data for reporting.

FIRST: Check if any features have last_edited_date within the last 10 days.

PROJECT:
{{ JSON.stringify($('All Projects1').item.json) }}

CYCLES AND FEATURES:
{{ JSON.stringify($json.data) }}

ALWAYS return the full JSON structure below. 
- If NO features edited in last 10 days: Set "skip": true and "reason": "No activity in last 10 days", leave other fields empty/default
- If features WERE edited in last 10 days: Set "skip": false and populate all fields

OUTPUT JSON STRUCTURE:
{
  "skip": false,
  "project_name": "",
  "reason": "",
  "project_status": "",
  "health_status": "On Track | Needs Attention | At Risk",
  "health_emoji": "🟢 | 🟡 | 🔴",
  "team": {
    "pm": {"name": "", "slack_id": ""},
    "developer": {"name": "", "slack_id": ""}
  },
  "metrics": {
    "completion_percentage": 0,
    "features_total": 0,
    "features_done": 0,
    "features_in_progress": 0,
    "features_not_started": 0,
    "features_blocked": 0,
    "features_overdue": 0
  },
  "completed_this_week": [
    {"name": "", "completed_by": ""}
  ],
  "in_progress": [
    {"name": "", "assigned_to": ""}
  ],
  "blockers": [
    {"feature": "", "reason": "", "days_blocked": 0, "owner": ""}
  ],
  "overdue": [
    {"feature": "", "due_date": "", "assigned_to": ""}
  ],
  "cycles": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "completion_percentage": 0,
      "features": [
        {"name": "", "status": ""}
      ]
    }
  ],
  "running_context": "",
  "next_week_focus": [""],
  "action_items": [
    {"action": "", "owner": ""}
  ]
}

